muxatmTrap.name: muxatmTrap
muxatmTrap.description: An enterprise-specific trap is generated when this MIB variable is read. If the trap is generated, the value of the MIB variable is 1. If the trap fails, the value of the MIB variable is 0.

muxatmString.name: muxatmString
muxatmString.description: A simple string. It is the title of the ATM MIB.

atmfAdapterTable.name: atmfAdapterTable
atmfAdapterTable.description: A table containing all information about the adapter.

atmfAdapterEntry.name: atmfAdapterEntry
atmfAdapterEntry.description: An entry in the table containing information about the adapter.

atmfAdapterIndex.name: atmfAdapterIndex
atmfAdapterIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this ATM adapter.

atmfAdapterSerialNumber.name: atmfAdapterSerialNumber
atmfAdapterSerialNumber.description: The serial number from the VPD of the ATM adapter.

atmfAdapterDiagVersion.name: atmfAdapterDiagVersion
atmfAdapterDiagVersion.description: The diagnostic version number from the VPD of the ATM adapter.

atmfAdapterSoftwareVersion.name: atmfAdapterSoftwareVersion
atmfAdapterSoftwareVersion.description: The software version number from the VPD of the ATM adapter.

atmfAdapterTransmitBufSize.name: atmfAdapterTransmitBufSize
atmfAdapterTransmitBufSize.description: The maximum transmit buffer size in bytes.

atmfAdapterReceiveBufSize.name: atmfAdapterReceiveBufSize
atmfAdapterReceiveBufSize.description: The maximum receive buffer size in bytes.

atmfAdapterTransmissionType.name: atmfAdapterTransmissionType
atmfAdapterTransmissionType.description: The Transmission type of this adapter. For example, for a adapter using the Sonet STS-3c physical layer at 155.52 Mbs, this object would have the Object Identifier Value:atmfSonetSTS3c. For the Turboways ATM 100 adapter this value shall be: atmf4B5B.

atmfAdapterMediaType.name: atmfAdapterMediaType
atmfAdapterMediaType.description: The type of media used on this port. For example, for a adapter using coaxial cable, this object would have the Object Identifier value: atmfMediaCoaxCable. For the Turboways ATM 100 adapter the media type shall be: atmfMediaMultiMode

atmfAdapterOperStatus.name: atmfAdapterOperStatus
atmfAdapterOperStatus.description: The operational (i.e., actual) state of this adapter. An alarm should not be generated on physical interface when the value of this object is outOfService(3). This capability is useful if equipment is to be disconnected, or for trouble shooting purposes. A value of loopBack(4) indicates that a local loopback is in place.

atmfAdapterType.name: atmfAdapterType
atmfAdapterType.description: The hardware type of this adapter. For example if the adapter is 100 Mbits MultiMode fiber adapter, then this object would have the Object Identifier value: atmfTurbowaysATM-100

atmfAtmLayerTable.name: atmfAtmLayerTable
atmfAtmLayerTable.description: A table containing ATM layer configuration information

atmfAtmLayerEntry.name: atmfAtmLayerEntry
atmfAtmLayerEntry.description: An entry in the table containing configuration information about the adapter.

atmfAtmLayerIndex.name: atmfAtmLayerIndex
atmfAtmLayerIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this ATM adapter.

atmfAtmLayerMaxVPCs.name: atmfAtmLayerMaxVPCs
atmfAtmLayerMaxVPCs.description: The maximum number of VPCs supported on this User to Network Interface.

atmfAtmLayerMaxVCCs.name: atmfAtmLayerMaxVCCs
atmfAtmLayerMaxVCCs.description: The maximum number of VCCs supported on this User to Network Interface.

atmfAtmLayerConfiguredVPCs.name: atmfAtmLayerConfiguredVPCs
atmfAtmLayerConfiguredVPCs.description: The number of VPCs configured for use on this User to Network Interface.

atmfAtmLayerConfiguredVCCs.name: atmfAtmLayerConfiguredVCCs
atmfAtmLayerConfiguredVCCs.description: The number of VCCs configured for use on this User to Network Interface.

atmfAtmLayerMaxVpiBits.name: atmfAtmLayerMaxVpiBits
atmfAtmLayerMaxVpiBits.description: The number of active VPI bits on this interface.

atmfAtmLayerMaxVciBits.name: atmfAtmLayerMaxVciBits
atmfAtmLayerMaxVciBits.description: The number of active VCI bits on this interface.

atmfAtmLayerUniType.name: atmfAtmLayerUniType
atmfAtmLayerUniType.description: The type of the ATM User to Network Interface, either public or private.

atmfAtmStatsTable.description: A table containing ATM layer statistics information.

atmfAtmStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table containing information about statistics.

atmfAtmStatsIndex.name: atmfAtmStatsIndex
atmfAtmStatsIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this ATM adapter.

atmfAtmStatsReceivedCells.name: atmfAtmStatsReceivedCells
atmfAtmStatsReceivedCells.description: The accumulated number of ATM cells received on this interface which were assigned and not dropped.

atmfAtmStatsDroppedPackets.name: atmfAtmStatsDroppedPackets
atmfAtmStatsDroppedPackets.description: The accumulated number of ATM packets which were dropped due to errors in the cell formatting.

atmfAtmStatsTransmittedCells.description: The accumulated number of assigned ATM cells which were transmitted across this interface.
